quran[19]{c,v,t,f}:
  15,52,"When they entered upon him and said, “Peace!” He said, “We are afraid of you<sup>23</sup>.”","[23] When he saw that their hands did not reach the roasted calf he presented to them."
  15,53,"They said, “Do not be afraid; We give you glad tidings of a knowledgeable boy<sup>24</sup>.”","[24] i.e., Isaac; of great religious knowledge."
  15,54,"He said, “Do you give me glad tidings despite my old age? What glad tidings are you giving me?”",""
  15,55,"They said, “We have given you glad tidings in truth, so do not be of those who despair<sup>25</sup>.”","[25] Abraham (عليه السلام) might have shown signs of doubt at believing such news."
  15,56,"He said, “Who would despair of his Lord’s mercy except those who are misguided<sup>26</sup>?”","[26] Abraham’s (عليه السلام) reply disproves the assumption that he was despondent of Allah’s Mercy."
  15,57,"He said, “So, what is your mission, O messengers?”",""
  15,58,"They said, “We have been sent to a wicked people<sup>27</sup>,","[27] i.e., the people of the prophet Lot (عليه السلام)."
  15,59,"except the household of Lot; we will surely save them all,",""
  15,60,"except his wife<sup>28</sup>; We have decreed that she will be among those who stay behind.”","[28] For she has collaborated with the evildoers."
  15,61,"When the messengers came to the household of Lot<sup>29</sup>,","[29] Details of the first three nations destroyed are given in this and the following verses, which were en route of the famous trading journeys of the Qurayshites: the people of Prophet Lot, those of the thicket (the people of Shu‘ayb), and those of Hegra (Madā’in Sālih)."
  15,62,"he said, “You are unfamiliar people.”",""
  15,63,"They said, “We have come to you with that [punishment]<sup>30</sup> which they have doubted.","[30] i.e., the divine punishment."
  15,64,"We have come to you with the truth, and we are certainly truthful.",""
  15,65,"So travel with your household in the dark of night and go behind them; none of you should look back<sup>31</sup>, and keep going to where you are commanded.”","[31] To be more persistent in their walk and strike some distance before dawn, or not to be frightened and traumatized by catching sight of the horrific punishment of their folks."
  15,66,"We conveyed this decree to him that these [people] will be exterminated by early morning.”",""
  15,67,"The people of the city came [to Lot] rejoicing<sup>32</sup>.","[32] At the news of his visitors."
  15,68,"Lot said, “These are my guests, so do not bring shame on me.",""
  15,69,"Fear Allah and do not disgrace me.”",""
  15,70,"They said, “Did we not forbid you from [protecting] people?”",""
